COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
    ('REL-A 314', 'GENDER AND POWER IN THE HEBREW BIBLE', '13208', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'BH 216', 'Laura Carlson Hasler', 3, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Traces the relationships among gender, sexuality, and political power in Jewish antiquity, primarily through the Hebrew Bible. Examines how fertility, virginity, sexuality, and foreignness intersect with gender-constructions in these texts. Demonstrates the diverse ways in which gender is depicted, attuned to differences in context and genre.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('REL-A 316', 'JEWS, CHRISTIANS, AND OTHERS IN LATE ANTIQUITY', '34076', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 5:30 PM–6:45 PM', 'GY 1043', 'Jeremy Schott', 2, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'GEOLOGICAL SCIENCES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Explores the interactions and so-called parting of the ways between Jews, Christians, and other religious groups in Roman Palestine and Sasanian Persia from the first through seventh centuries C.E. Pays special attention to the portrayals of Christians in Jewish literature such as the Mishnah and Talmud.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit
COLL (CASE) Culture Studies: Global Civ & Culture'], NULL),
    ('REL-A 450', 'TOPICS IN THE HISTORY OF CHRISTIANITY', '13221', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'SY 006', 'Patrick Michelson', 7, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'SYCAMORE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Significant figures, issues, and movements in the history of Christianity examined in their social and religious contexts, with attention to their continuing religious and cultural impact.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('REL-A 470', 'TOPICS IN ISLAMIC STUDIES', '29351', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'BH 344', 'Robert Jaques', 13, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Selected topics on Islamic law, philosophy, theology, and mysticism.', ARRAY['COLL (CASE) A&H Breadth of Inquiry credit'], NULL),
    ('REL-B 210', 'INTRODUCTION TO BUDDHISM', '11960', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 5:30 PM–6:45 PM', 'BH 110', 'Richard Nance', 3, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'BALLANTINE HALL', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introduction to the basic beliefs and practices of Buddhism from its beginnings to the present. Special attention to the life and teachings of the founder, significant developments in India, and the diffusion of the tradition to East Asia, Central Asia, and the West.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
