    ('REL-B 220', 'INTRODUCTION TO HINDUISM', '13207', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'GA 0001', 'Rebecca Manring', 13, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'GLOBAL & INTERNATIONAL STUDIES', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Beliefs, rites, and institutions of Hinduism from the Vedic (c. 1200 B.C.) to modern times: religion of the Vedas and the Upanishads, epics and the rise of devotional religion, philosophical systems (Yoga and Vedanta), sectarian theism, monasticism, socioreligious institutions, popular religion (temples and pilgrimages), modern Hindu syncretism.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd A&H credit
IUB GenEd World Culture credit
